PoS is the sacrifice of TRUST for speed. 

In PoS protocols, the more money you have the greater your ability to edit/change the ledger/TRUTH!

THIS IS A PROBLEM

In #bitcoin's proof of work protocol, no matter how much #bitcoin you acquire you can't change the TRUTH!

What makes the #bitcoin yours is that only you have access to the private key, that is what your "wallet" holds. 

This private key gives you the sole ability to move that #bitcoin to another address (spend it). While speed is important, TRUST is even more important.

When #bitcoin is sent to someone it doesn't suddenly arrive on their phone/USB/wallet. 

A transaction just updates the distributed ledger to say that this wallet owns this amount of #bitcoin. 

Millions of computers are competing to keep track of this ledger and your BTC via PoW

Many cryptocurrencies love talking about "speed", but TRUST > "Speed"

The whole point of money was to effectively keep track of who owns what and give people a common unit of account to track that ownership.

Here is how #bitcoin + PoW does that and how others fall short.
